WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-CA

00:00:00.734 --> 00:00:03.002
So, in this video, I'm
gonna draw a small table.

00:00:03.003 --> 00:00:05.505
But before we get
started, I want to change

00:00:05.506 --> 00:00:08.007
a few of the settings.
So, by default,

00:00:08.008 --> 00:00:11.077
we are in the
architectural style.

00:00:11.078 --> 00:00:13.913
And the architectural style
has got these thick lines

00:00:13.914 --> 00:00:17.016
with a kind of a little
marker on all the corners.

00:00:17.017 --> 00:00:18.412
And if you're
designing something

00:00:18.433 --> 00:00:19.519
like a piece
of furniture,

00:00:19.520 --> 00:00:22.455
that's really not ideal,
so let's go under Window

00:00:22.456 --> 00:00:26.392
Styles and I'll
select the...

00:00:26.393 --> 00:00:28.027
the Engineering
style.

00:00:28.028 --> 00:00:31.497
And that takes away the horizon
and it makes the lines

00:00:31.498 --> 00:00:34.167
nice and thin,
which is ideal.

00:00:34.168 --> 00:00:37.470
Next thing we
want to do is

00:00:37.471 --> 00:00:40.973
change the units. By default,
SketchUp likes to be

00:00:40.974 --> 00:00:44.911
in inches, I've already changed
this over to be in metric.

00:00:44.912 --> 00:00:48.514
So I want to be in Decimal and I
like to design in Centimeters.

00:00:48.515 --> 00:00:53.457
And I'll set the precision
to be 0.1 centimeters.

00:00:53.520 --> 00:00:55.955
And Length Snapping of .1
centimeter, 1 millimeter,

00:00:55.956 --> 00:00:57.723
that works out
very well.

00:00:57.724 --> 00:00:59.959
So, it's really important
that you set your units

00:00:59.960 --> 00:01:03.162
especially metric versus
imperial before you get started,

00:01:03.163 --> 00:01:06.232
because if you switch
between metric and imperial

00:01:06.233 --> 00:01:08.000
after you start a drawing,
nothing works out to a

00:01:08.001 --> 00:01:10.136
nice and
round unit.

00:01:10.137 --> 00:01:12.205
OK, now that we're
done setting up,

00:01:12.206 --> 00:01:14.073
we have Susan here.

00:01:14.074 --> 00:01:17.944
She's part of the default
set-up when you start SketchUp.

00:01:17.945 --> 00:01:20.012
She's kind of shallow. She's
really just a silhouette but

00:01:20.013 --> 00:01:21.747
she's always
facing us.

00:01:21.748 --> 00:01:23.983
It's good to keep her around
while you're getting started

00:01:23.984 --> 00:01:27.153
because she gives you a
nice sense of perspective.

00:01:27.154 --> 00:01:30.723
So, I'm gonna start my
table by drawing a leg.

00:01:30.724 --> 00:01:36.095
And I want that leg to be 4.5
by 4.5 centimeters so...

00:01:36.096 --> 00:01:38.883
I'm gonna draw,
just a rectangle.

00:01:38.932 --> 00:01:41.000
And you'll notice in
the bottom right,

00:01:41.001 --> 00:01:43.302
that the dimensions
are displayed.

00:01:43.303 --> 00:01:46.506
So, I'm going to click
on here and then

00:01:46.507 --> 00:01:53.112
enter 4.5, 4.5 that means I
want the rectangle to be

00:01:53.113 --> 00:01:55.548
4.5 by 4.5
centimeters.

00:01:55.549 --> 00:01:57.517
When I push enter,

00:01:57.518 --> 00:01:59.986
the rectangle
becomes that size.

00:01:59.987 --> 00:02:02.121
So, let's zoom in
on that a bit.

00:02:02.122 --> 00:02:03.411
So, basically
there's our

00:02:03.432 --> 00:02:05.358
rectangle. Now to
create a solid,

00:02:05.559 --> 00:02:07.960
we use the
push/pull tool

00:02:07.961 --> 00:02:10.463
or extrude tool as other
people may call it.

00:02:10.464 --> 00:02:14.233
And I'm gonna turn this
and extrude it into

00:02:14.234 --> 00:02:18.104
a solid shape, and I
want that shape...

00:02:18.105 --> 00:02:20.306
I want that leg to be
70 centimeters long.

00:02:20.307 --> 00:02:22.408
Now notice again on
the bottom right

00:02:22.409 --> 00:02:26.746
it shows how long it currently
is and if I type in 70,

00:02:26.747 --> 00:02:30.550
that becomes exactly
70 centimeters long.

00:02:30.551 --> 00:02:33.619
So, there's
our table leg

00:02:33.620 --> 00:02:38.191
Now I want to draw some
apron rails for this table.

00:02:38.192 --> 00:02:41.961
So, I'm going to again
draw a rectangle.

00:02:41.962 --> 00:02:46.265
And let's draw this. And I
want that apron rail to be

00:02:46.266 --> 00:02:50.824
1.9 thick by about 8
centimeters wide.

00:02:51.872 --> 00:02:53.706
So, we're close to that
on the bottom right,

00:02:53.707 --> 00:02:57.966
but I'll enter
that as 8, 1.9.

00:02:58.512 --> 00:03:00.580
And now let's
extrude that out,

00:03:00.581 --> 00:03:04.083
and I want that 60
centimeters long.

00:03:04.084 --> 00:03:08.154
Now, you'll notice that this
has just become one shape,

00:03:08.155 --> 00:03:12.465
in fact it's impossible for
me to move this part here.

00:03:12.526 --> 00:03:15.595
I can't even move this thing
because it's, kind of, stuck

00:03:15.596 --> 00:03:18.931
to the leg. So, this
is our next thing,

00:03:18.932 --> 00:03:22.268
we need objects. So, I'm gonna
hit backspace a few times,

00:03:22.269 --> 00:03:24.704
to undo what
I've just done.

00:03:24.705 --> 00:03:28.207
And I'm gonna turn this
leg into an object,

00:03:28.208 --> 00:03:31.143
so that the next thing that I
draw doesn't become stuck to it.

00:03:31.144 --> 00:03:33.713
So, I'll
triple-click on it.

00:03:33.714 --> 00:03:36.282
And then I'll
select this tool.

00:03:36.283 --> 00:03:38.602
And I'll call
that Table Leg.

00:03:40.354 --> 00:03:43.122
So this is now
an object.

00:03:43.123 --> 00:03:44.761
And if I want to
edit this thing,

00:03:44.782 --> 00:03:46.158
I have to
double-click on it

00:03:46.159 --> 00:03:48.995
to open it and now I
can do things to it.

00:03:48.996 --> 00:03:51.931
But I'm gonna leave this
leg as it is for now.

00:03:51.932 --> 00:03:55.635
So now, once again, let's
draw our apron rail.

00:03:55.636 --> 00:03:58.504
And I can draw this
on the face here.

00:03:58.505 --> 00:04:02.808
And I'm gonna draw
this at 8, 1.9.

00:04:02.809 --> 00:04:05.824
And I'll extrude that
out 60 centimeters.

00:04:07.714 --> 00:04:10.532
So there's our
apron rail.

00:04:11.151 --> 00:04:14.179
Now let's make
that an object.

00:04:14.555 --> 00:04:16.622
So, triple-click on it
to select all that.

00:04:16.623 --> 00:04:19.125
Notice that it doesn't select
the leg, because the leg

00:04:19.126 --> 00:04:20.626
is in it's
own object.

00:04:20.627 --> 00:04:23.996
And the triple-click doesn't
select things into the object.

00:04:23.997 --> 00:04:26.766
So, create an
object of that.

00:04:26.767 --> 00:04:29.202
So, there's our
apron rail.

00:04:29.203 --> 00:04:32.405
And now let's
take that leg,

00:04:32.406 --> 00:04:36.142
and make a copy of it. And I'm
holding down Control as I

00:04:36.143 --> 00:04:38.878
drag this along, and
you'll notice the line

00:04:38.879 --> 00:04:41.280
that I'm dragging
along is red.

00:04:41.281 --> 00:04:44.150
Basically, if I'm dragging along
an axis and it snaps to that,

00:04:44.151 --> 00:04:45.852
here's along the
green axis.

00:04:45.853 --> 00:04:48.921
Here's along
the red axis.

00:04:48.922 --> 00:04:52.291
That will drag it along the
axis nice and parallel.

00:04:52.292 --> 00:04:54.794
So, now I've got
two legs here.

00:04:54.795 --> 00:04:57.730
Now, the apron rail doesn't
look very good if it's just

00:04:57.731 --> 00:05:01.234
flush with the table leg. So,
I'm gonna take this apron rail,

00:05:01.235 --> 00:05:04.470
I'll select the Move
tool, and I will move it

00:05:04.471 --> 00:05:08.174
in a little bit. And because
I like to keep things nice

00:05:08.175 --> 00:05:11.277
and known dimensions, I want
that half a centimeter.

00:05:11.278 --> 00:05:14.747
So, if you'd watch on the
bottom right, I can drag that

00:05:14.748 --> 00:05:18.900
to .5 centimeters. It's a
bit tricky to do that.

00:05:18.919 --> 00:05:21.620
It's easier to just punch
in the number that I want.

00:05:22.623 --> 00:05:24.757
So now we
have two legs

00:05:24.758 --> 00:05:29.328
for our table. So, now let's
create another apron rail.

00:05:29.329 --> 00:05:32.398
Now we've already got
this apron rail here.

00:05:32.399 --> 00:05:35.535
And I just need to
rotate that around

00:05:35.536 --> 00:05:37.470
to get one on
this side.

00:05:37.471 --> 00:05:41.007
So, let's rotate
that apron rail.

00:05:41.008 --> 00:05:43.309
So, I'm gonna select
the apron rail.

00:05:43.310 --> 00:05:46.145
And select the
rotate tool.

00:05:46.146 --> 00:05:48.447
And I'm just gonna
put...go on this face.

00:05:48.448 --> 00:05:51.517
Now I notice this
circle is blue.

00:05:51.518 --> 00:05:54.654
And that's because we're
rotating about the blue axis.

00:05:54.655 --> 00:05:56.522
And I'll
rotate...Oops.

00:05:56.523 --> 00:05:58.486
OK, now I've just
rotated that but

00:05:58.507 --> 00:06:00.393
I actually wanted
to make a copy.

00:06:00.394 --> 00:06:02.828
So undo that.

00:06:02.829 --> 00:06:06.699
And now I'm gonna hit control
and again rotate that,

00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:09.035
and now I'm
copying.

00:06:09.036 --> 00:06:12.972
Now that rail is not exactly
where we want it to be.

00:06:12.973 --> 00:06:16.609
So let's use the move tool and
I'll take to the corner of it.

00:06:16.610 --> 00:06:20.112
And now drag that
to the corner...

00:06:20.113 --> 00:06:23.249
here. And it's snapped
to that corner

00:06:23.250 --> 00:06:26.018
And now let's move it in
by half a centimeter.

00:06:26.019 --> 00:06:28.754
And I'm just gonna
enter that, .5.

00:06:28.755 --> 00:06:32.124
And there is our
second apron rail.

00:06:32.125 --> 00:06:35.761
Now, let's
take the legs,

00:06:35.762 --> 00:06:37.964
an apron rail that
we've already got,

00:06:37.965 --> 00:06:40.533
and we need to
copy that over

00:06:40.534 --> 00:06:42.401
to create the next
pair of legs, so...

00:06:42.402 --> 00:06:45.137
I'll use this
Move tool,

00:06:45.138 --> 00:06:51.110
I'll hit Control,
and I'll move it.

00:06:51.111 --> 00:06:54.480
And there's our
next set of rails.

00:06:54.481 --> 00:06:58.184
Now, you'll notice that the
apron rail is on the inside.

00:06:58.185 --> 00:07:00.486
I could just
move that.

00:07:00.487 --> 00:07:03.923
But I actually want to
flip this whole thing

00:07:03.924 --> 00:07:05.992
so that when I go on
and do the joinery,

00:07:05.993 --> 00:07:09.228
the orientation is correct.
So, I'm gonna

00:07:09.229 --> 00:07:11.297
right-click
on this,

00:07:11.298 --> 00:07:15.001
flip long and I'm gonna
do the green direction.

00:07:15.002 --> 00:07:17.737
So there we go.

00:07:17.738 --> 00:07:21.941
And now let's take
this apron rail,

00:07:21.942 --> 00:07:24.143
and again

00:07:24.144 --> 00:07:28.147
Control Drag,
to move it.

00:07:28.148 --> 00:07:31.584
Zooming in here, put
if flush, and now

00:07:31.585 --> 00:07:37.429
.5 centimeters, and there
we have our apron rails.

00:07:37.991 --> 00:07:41.794
And Susan is standing right
in the middle of our table.

00:07:41.795 --> 00:07:43.729
We now have a pretty
good sense of scale,

00:07:43.730 --> 00:07:46.599
for this little table here so we
really don't need Susan anymore,

00:07:46.600 --> 00:07:51.437
so let's select Susan
and delete her.

00:07:51.438 --> 00:07:54.307
So, now we need a
top for our table.

00:07:54.308 --> 00:07:57.009
Do I'm gonna
select the

00:07:57.010 --> 00:08:02.148
square rectangle tool
and I'm gonna draw

00:08:02.149 --> 00:08:06.085
a rectangle or a square
right on top of the table.

00:08:06.086 --> 00:08:11.457
And now we have essentially
just a 2-dimensional surface.

00:08:11.458 --> 00:08:13.893
So, let's
select this,

00:08:13.894 --> 00:08:15.767
use the push/pull
tool and I want

00:08:15.788 --> 00:08:17.530
that to be 2
centimeters thick.

00:08:17.531 --> 00:08:21.234
So I'm gonna drag
this, pull it off,

00:08:21.235 --> 00:08:23.903
and I'm gonna enter
2 centimeters.

00:08:23.904 --> 00:08:26.472
And there is
the table top.

00:08:26.473 --> 00:08:29.208
Now that really doesn't
look very good.

00:08:29.209 --> 00:08:31.344
I actually want
that table top

00:08:31.345 --> 00:08:34.080
to overhang the edges a
little bit, so I'm gonna

00:08:34.081 --> 00:08:37.717
select this edge here and
again use the push/pull tool.

00:08:37.718 --> 00:08:40.419
I'm gonna drag it out
by 5 centimeters.

00:08:40.420 --> 00:08:43.289
I'm just gonna enter that.
And I'll do that

00:08:43.290 --> 00:08:48.327
on every side. And
drag that out.

00:08:48.328 --> 00:08:51.197
5 centimeters. Now an
interesting thing is

00:08:51.198 --> 00:08:53.232
if we have nothing
selected,

00:08:53.233 --> 00:08:55.601
and we select the
push/pull tool,

00:08:55.602 --> 00:08:57.503
it will apply to whatever
we have the mouse on top.

00:08:57.504 --> 00:09:00.273
So I can just do
this, 5 centimeters,

00:09:00.274 --> 00:09:02.542
and then move around, I don't
have to do separate select

00:09:02.543 --> 00:09:05.978
I can just again, go
here and 5 centimeters.

00:09:05.979 --> 00:09:09.048
And there we have

00:09:09.049 --> 00:09:12.618
a nice little
card table.

00:09:12.619 --> 00:09:16.322
In the next video,I'm
gonna do some joinery

00:09:16.323 --> 00:09:18.824
to actually do the joints
that connect this thing,

00:09:18.825 --> 00:09:20.901
and embellish the
table a little bit.

